Cape Town - The Muizenberg Family Violence, Child Protection and Sexual Offences Unit (FCS) is seeking the assistance of the public in locating a suspect who is wanted in connection with a sexual assault of a 7-year-old girl in Hout Bay. The incident allegedly took place on Tuesday, 1 January 2019. The suspect is Madalitso Khanyoza, 23-years-old who is currently on the run. A warrant of arrest has been issued for his arrest. Police urge anyone who can assist in finding the wanted suspect to kindly contact the investigating officer Detective Sergeant De Jager on 082 522 1075 or 021 784 2736 alternatively Crime Stop at 08600 10111. All information will be treated as highly confidential. In an unrelated matter, SAPS revealed that Someleze Nkente, a 11-year-old boy from Langa, who went missing after playing with other children next to his home was found dead at the mortuary on Monday. He was knocked down by the car alongside the N2. Cape Argus